data.name: scale_mix.ToolTip
data.value: the "Mixed" mode downscales the image to double of the final resolution with lanczos, and then downscales to the final resolution with nearest neighbor. The advantage is that has less aliasing than nearest, and isnt as blurry as lanczos

data.name: surround.ToolTip
data.value: If the input file uses Surround sound, the homebrew app will not be able to play the audio track Enabling this option will downmix it to stereo (Credit to Dave_750 for the filter) Enable ONLY if your input is surround, or it will throw error!!!
